d":"23","subdivision_name_de":"17. Jh.","subdivision_name_en":"17th century"},"literatur":"F. Freiherr von Schr\u00f6tter, Die M\u00fcnzen Friedrich Wilhelms des Gro\u00dfen Kurf\u00fcrsten und Friedrichs III. von Brandenburg (1913) Nr. 2181 (dieses St\u00fcck).","comment":"Kurf\u00fcrstin Luise Henriette (1627-1667), geborene Gr\u00e4fin von Oranien-Nassau, hatte mit 19 Jahren Friedrich Wilhelm, den Gro\u00dfen Kurf\u00fcrsten geheiratet. Aus den fortschrittlichen Niederlanden stammend, war sie ihrem Mann eine wichtige politische Beraterin. 1650 schenkte ihr der Kurf\u00fcrst das Amt B\u00f6tzow bei Berlin, wo sie sich an die Stelle eines alten Jagdschlosses ein neues Schloss im holl\u00e4ndischen Stil erbauen lie\u00df und es 'Oranienburg' nannte. Der Ort nahm sp\u00e4ter diesen Namen an. Die Kurf\u00fcrstin war die Mutter des ersten preu\u00dfischen K\u00f6nigs Friedrich I. Auf ihren Tod 1667 wurden verschiedene Gedenkm\u00fcnzen gepr\u00e4gt.","period":{"ikmk_period_id":"13","name_de":"Barock","name_en":"Baroque","description_de":"Kunst bzw- Stilperiode, welche mit regional unterschiedlichen Entwicklungen die Zeit vom Ende des 16. Jahrhunderts ist ca. 1730 umfasst. Teilweise wird der Rokoko (bis ca. 1770) ihr auch zugerechnet.","description_en":"Art period with a regionally varying developement in chronological terms roughly from the end of the 16th century to c. 1730. Sometimes the following period Rococo (to c. 1770) is considered a late form of Baroque.","concept_id":"http:\/\/vocab.getty.edu\/aat\/300021147","ndp_uri":"https:\/\/ikmk.smb.museum\/ndp\/period\/13"},"year_start":"1667","year_end":"1667","date_verbal":"1667","year_islam":"0","references":[{"ikmk_referenz_id":181,"souce":"Schr\u00f6tter Gro\u00dfer Kurf\u00fcrst","number":"2181","similar":"0"}],"manufacturing":[{"ikmk_manufacturing_id":"21","manufacturing_name_de":"gepr\u00e4gt","manufacturing_name_en":"struck","nomisma_id":"http:\/\/nomisma.org\/id\/struck","ndp_uri":"https:\/\/ikmk.smb.museum\/ndp\/manufacture\/21"}],"linked_persons_corporations":{"54":{"ikmk_type_id":"54","type_name_de":"Dargestellte\/r","type_name_en":"Sitter","type_nomisma_id":"http:\/\/nomisma.org\/id\/portrait","type_concept_id":"http:\/\/vocab.getty.edu\/aat\/300189844","ndp_id":"https:\/\/ikmk.smb.museum\/ndp\/type_for_person_and_corporation\/54","items":{"3784":{"ikmk_person_id":"3784","title_de":null,"first_name_de":null,"last_name_de":"Luise Henriette (1646-1667), Kurf\u00fcrstin von Brandenburg","vitalDates":"07.12.1627 - 18.06.1667","title_en":null,"first_name_en":null,"last_name_en":"Louise Henriette (1646-1667), electress of Brandenburg","corporation":"0","lod":{"https:\/\/d-nb.info\/gnd\/118969080":"https:\/\/d-nb.info\/gnd\/118969080","https:\/\/de.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Luise_Henriette_von_Oranien":"https:\/\/de.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Luise_Henriette_von_Oranien","https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Countess_Louise_Henriette_of_Nassau":"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Countess_Louise_Henriette_of_Nassau","https:\/\/viaf.org\/viaf\/74653010":"https:\/\/viaf.org\/viaf\/74653010","https:\/\/www.wikidata.org\/wiki\/Q196301":"https:\/\/www.wikidata.org\/wiki\/Q196301","https:\/\/ikmk.smb.museum\/ndp\/person\/3784":"https:\/\/ikmk.smb.museum\/ndp\/person\/3784"}}}},"56":{"ikmk_type_id":"56","type_name_de":"M\u00fcnzwardein","type_name_en":"Warden","type_nomisma_id":"","type_concept_id":"http:\/\/d-nb.info\/gnd\/7785784-7","ndp_id":"https:\/\/ikmk.smb.museum\/ndp\/type_for_person_and_corporation\/56","items":{"3319":{"ikmk_person_id":"3319","title_de":"","first_name_de":"Jobst","last_name_de":"Liebmann","vitalDates":"","title_en":null,"first_name_en":"Jobst","last_name_en":"Liebmann","corporation":"0","lod":{"https:\/\/ikmk.smb.museum\/ndp\/person\/3319":"https:\/\/ikmk.smb.museum\/ndp\/person\/3319"}}}},"57":{"ikmk_type_id":"57","type_name_de":"Autorit\u00e4t","type_name_en":"Authority","type_nomisma_id":"http:\/\/nomisma.org\/id\/authority","type_concept_id":"http:\/\/d-nb.info\/g